  27 class OrganizationEventsV2EndpointTest(APITestCase, SnubaTestCase):
  28     def setUp(self):
  29         super(OrganizationEventsV2EndpointTest, self).setUp()
  30         self.min_ago = iso_format(before_now(minutes=1))
  31         self.two_min_ago = iso_format(before_now(minutes=2))
  32         self.url = reverse(
  33             "sentry-api-0-organization-eventsv2",
  34             kwargs={"organization_slug": self.organization.slug},
  35         )
  36 
  37     def test_no_projects(self):
  38         self.login_as(user=self.user)
  39         with self.feature("organizations:discover-basic"):
  40             response = self.client.get(self.url, format="json")
  41 
  42         assert response.status_code == 200, response.content
  43         assert len(response.data) == 0
  44 
  45     def test_or_errors(self):
  46         self.login_as(user=self.user)
  47         self.create_project()
  48 
  49         with self.feature("organizations:discover-basic"):
  50             response = self.client.get(
  51                 self.url,
  52                 {"field": ["id"], "query": "user.email:test OR user.email:foo"},
  53                 format="json",
  54             )
  55 
  56         assert response.status_code == 400

  58     def test_performance_view_feature(self):
  59         self.login_as(user=self.user)
  60         self.store_event(
  61             data={"event_id": "a" * 32, "timestamp": self.min_ago, "fingerprint": ["group1"]},
  62             project_id=self.project.id,
  63         )
  64 
  65         query = {"field": ["id", "project.id"], "project": [self.project.id]}
  66         with self.feature(
  67             {"organizations:discover-basic": False, "organizations:performance-view": True}
  68         ):
  69             response = self.client.get(self.url, query, format="json")
  70         assert response.status_code == 200
  71         assert len(response.data["data"]) == 1

  73     def test_multi_project_feature_gate_rejection(self):
  74         self.login_as(user=self.user)
  75         team = self.create_team(organization=self.organization, members=[self.user])
  76 
  77         project = self.create_project(organization=self.organization, teams=[team])
  78         project2 = self.create_project(organization=self.organization, teams=[team])
  79 
  80         self.store_event(
  81             data={"event_id": "a" * 32, "timestamp": self.min_ago, "fingerprint": ["group1"]},
  82             project_id=project.id,
  83         )
  84         self.store_event(
  85             data={"event_id": "b" * 32, "timestamp": self.min_ago, "fingerprint": ["group2"]},
  86             project_id=project2.id,
  87         )
  88 
  89         query = {"field": ["id", "project.id"], "project": [project.id, project2.id]}
  90         with self.feature(
  91             {"organizations:discover-basic": True, "organizations:global-views": False}
  92         ):
  93             response = self.client.get(self.url, query, format="json")
  94         assert response.status_code == 400
  95         assert "events from multiple projects" in response.data["detail"]

  97     def test_invalid_search_terms(self):
  98         self.login_as(user=self.user)
  99 
 100         project = self.create_project()
 101         self.store_event(
 102             data={"event_id": "a" * 32, "message": "how to make fast", "timestamp": self.min_ago},
 103             project_id=project.id,
 104         )
 105 
 106         with self.feature("organizations:discover-basic"):
 107             response = self.client.get(
 108                 self.url, {"field": ["id"], "query": "hi \n there"}, format="json"
 109             )
 110 
 111         assert response.status_code == 400, response.content
 112         assert (
 113             response.data["detail"]
 114             == "Parse error at 'hi \n ther' (column 4). This is commonly caused by unmatched parentheses. Enclose any text in double quotes."
 115         )

 117     @patch("sentry.snuba.discover.raw_query")
 118     def test_handling_snuba_errors(self, mock_query):
 119         mock_query.side_effect = RateLimitExceeded("test")
 120 
 121         self.login_as(user=self.user)
 122         project = self.create_project()
 123 
 124         self.store_event(
 125             data={"event_id": "a" * 32, "message": "how to make fast"}, project_id=project.id
 126         )
 127 
 128         with self.feature("organizations:discover-basic"):
 129             response = self.client.get(
 130                 self.url,
 131                 data={"field": ["id", "timestamp"], "orderby": ["-timestamp", "-id"]},
 132                 format="json",
 133             )
 134 
 135         assert response.status_code == 400, response.content
 136         assert (
 137             response.data["detail"]
 138             == "Query timeout. Please try again. If the problem persists try a smaller date range or fewer projects."
 139         )
 140 
 141         mock_query.side_effect = QueryExecutionError("test")
 142         with self.feature("organizations:discover-basic"):
 143             response = self.client.get(
 144                 self.url,
 145                 data={"field": ["id", "timestamp"], "orderby": ["-timestamp", "-id"]},
 146                 format="json",
 147             )
 148 
 149         assert response.status_code == 400, response.content
 150         assert response.data["detail"] == "Internal error. Your query failed to run."
 151 
 152         mock_query.side_effect = QueryIllegalTypeOfArgument("test")
 153         with self.feature("organizations:discover-basic"):
 154             response = self.client.get(
 155                 self.url,
 156                 data={"field": ["id", "timestamp"], "orderby": ["-timestamp", "-id"]},
 157                 format="json",
 158             )
 159 
 160         assert response.status_code == 400, response.content
 161         assert response.data["detail"] == "Invalid query. Argument to function is wrong type."

 163     def test_out_of_retention(self):
 164         self.login_as(user=self.user)
 165         self.create_project()
 166         with self.options({"system.event-retention-days": 10}):
 167             with self.feature("organizations:discover-basic"):
 168                 response = self.client.get(
 169                     self.url,
 170                     data={
 171                         "field": ["id", "timestamp"],
 172                         "orderby": ["-timestamp", "-id"],
 173                         "start": iso_format(before_now(days=20)),
 174                         "end": iso_format(before_now(days=15)),
 175                     },
 176                     format="json",
 177                 )
 178 
 179         assert response.status_code == 400, response.content
 180         assert response.data["detail"] == "Invalid date range. Please try a more recent date range."

 182     def test_raw_data(self):
 183         self.login_as(user=self.user)
 184         project = self.create_project()
 185         self.store_event(
 186             data={
 187                 "event_id": "a" * 32,
 188                 "environment": "staging",
 189                 "timestamp": self.two_min_ago,
 190                 "user": {"ip_address": "127.0.0.1", "email": "foo@example.com"},
 191             },
 192             project_id=project.id,
 193         )
 194         self.store_event(
 195             data={
 196                 "event_id": "b" * 32,
 197                 "environment": "staging",
 198                 "timestamp": self.min_ago,
 199                 "user": {"ip_address": "127.0.0.1", "email": "foo@example.com"},
 200             },
 201             project_id=project.id,
 202         )
 203 
 204         with self.feature("organizations:discover-basic"):
 205             response = self.client.get(
 206                 self.url,
 207                 format="json",
 208                 data={
 209                     "field": ["id", "project.id", "user.email", "user.ip", "timestamp"],
 210                     "orderby": "-timestamp",
 211                 },
 212             )
 213 
 214         assert response.status_code == 200, response.content
 215         data = response.data["data"]
 216         assert len(data) == 2
 217         assert data[0]["id"] == "b" * 32
 218         assert data[0]["project.id"] == project.id
 219         assert data[0]["user.email"] == "foo@example.com"
 220         meta = response.data["meta"]
 221         assert meta["id"] == "string"
 222         assert meta["user.email"] == "string"
 223         assert meta["user.ip"] == "string"
 224         assert meta["timestamp"] == "date"

 366     def test_user_search(self):
 367         self.login_as(user=self.user)
 368 
 369         project = self.create_project()
 370         data = load_data("transaction", timestamp=before_now(minutes=1))
 371         data["user"] = {
 372             "email": "foo@example.com",
 373             "id": "123",
 374             "ip_address": "127.0.0.1",
 375             "username": "foo",
 376         }
 377         self.store_event(data, project_id=project.id)
 378 
 379         with self.feature(
 380             {"organizations:discover-basic": True, "organizations:global-views": True}
 381         ):
 382             for value in data["user"].values():
 383                 response = self.client.get(
 384                     self.url,
 385                     format="json",
 386                     data={
 387                         "field": ["project", "user"],
 388                         "query": "user:{}".format(value),
 389                         "statsPeriod": "14d",
 390                     },
 391                 )
 392 
 393                 assert response.status_code == 200, response.content
 394                 assert len(response.data["data"]) == 1
 395                 assert response.data["data"][0]["project"] == project.slug
 396                 assert response.data["data"][0]["user"] == data["user"]["email"]

 419     def test_has_issue(self):
 420         self.login_as(user=self.user)
 421 
 422         project = self.create_project()
 423         event = self.store_event(
 424             {"timestamp": iso_format(before_now(minutes=1))}, project_id=project.id
 425         )
 426 
 427         data = load_data("transaction", timestamp=before_now(minutes=1))
 428         self.store_event(data, project_id=project.id)
 429 
 430         with self.feature(
 431             {"organizations:discover-basic": True, "organizations:global-views": True}
 432         ):
 433             response = self.client.get(
 434                 self.url,
 435                 format="json",
 436                 data={"field": ["project", "issue"], "query": "has:issue", "statsPeriod": "14d"},
 437             )
 438 
 439         assert response.status_code == 200, response.content
 440         assert len(response.data["data"]) == 1
 441         assert response.data["data"][0]["issue"] == event.group.qualified_short_id
 442 
 443         with self.feature(
 444             {"organizations:discover-basic": True, "organizations:global-views": True}
 445         ):
 446             response = self.client.get(
 447                 self.url,
 448                 format="json",
 449                 data={"field": ["project", "issue"], "query": "!has:issue", "statsPeriod": "14d"},
 450             )
 451 
 452         assert response.status_code == 200, response.content
 453         assert len(response.data["data"]) == 1
 454         assert response.data["data"][0]["issue"] == "unknown"

 456     def test_negative_user_search(self):
 457         self.login_as(user=self.user)
 458 
 459         project = self.create_project()
 460         user_data = {"email": "foo@example.com", "id": "123", "username": "foo"}
 461 
 462         # Load events with data that shouldn't match
 463         for key in user_data:
 464             data = load_data("transaction", timestamp=before_now(minutes=1))
 465             data["transaction"] = "/transactions/{}".format(key)
 466             event_data = user_data.copy()
 467             event_data[key] = "undefined"
 468             data["user"] = event_data
 469             self.store_event(data, project_id=project.id)
 470 
 471         # Load a matching event
 472         data = load_data("transaction", timestamp=before_now(minutes=1))
 473         data["transaction"] = "/transactions/matching"
 474         data["user"] = user_data
 475         self.store_event(data, project_id=project.id)
 476 
 477         with self.feature(
 478             {"organizations:discover-basic": True, "organizations:global-views": True}
 479         ):
 480             response = self.client.get(
 481                 self.url,
 482                 format="json",
 483                 data={
 484                     "field": ["project", "user"],
 485                     "query": "!user:undefined",
 486                     "statsPeriod": "14d",
 487                 },
 488             )
 489 
 490             assert response.status_code == 200, response.content
 491             assert len(response.data["data"]) == 1
 492             assert response.data["data"][0]["user"] == user_data["email"]
 493             assert "user.email" not in response.data["data"][0]

 526     def test_implicit_groupby(self):
 527         self.login_as(user=self.user)
 528         project = self.create_project()
 529         self.store_event(
 530             data={"event_id": "a" * 32, "timestamp": self.two_min_ago, "fingerprint": ["group_1"]},
 531             project_id=project.id,
 532         )
 533         event1 = self.store_event(
 534             data={"event_id": "b" * 32, "timestamp": self.min_ago, "fingerprint": ["group_1"]},
 535             project_id=project.id,
 536         )
 537         event2 = self.store_event(
 538             data={"event_id": "c" * 32, "timestamp": self.min_ago, "fingerprint": ["group_2"]},
 539             project_id=project.id,
 540         )
 541 
 542         with self.feature("organizations:discover-basic"):
 543             response = self.client.get(
 544                 self.url,
 545                 format="json",
 546                 data={"field": ["count(id)", "project.id", "issue.id"], "orderby": "issue.id"},
 547             )
 548 
 549         assert response.status_code == 200, response.content
 550         assert len(response.data["data"]) == 2
 551         data = response.data["data"]
 552         assert data[0] == {
 553             "project.id": project.id,
 554             "project.name": project.slug,
 555             "issue.id": event1.group_id,
 556             "count_id": 2,
 557             "latest_event": event1.event_id,
 558         }
 559         assert data[1] == {
 560             "project.id": project.id,
 561             "project.name": project.slug,
 562             "issue.id": event2.group_id,
 563             "count_id": 1,
 564             "latest_event": event2.event_id,
 565         }
 566         meta = response.data["meta"]
 567         assert meta["count_id"] == "integer"

 569     def test_automatic_id_and_project(self):
 570         self.login_as(user=self.user)
 571         project = self.create_project()
 572         self.store_event(
 573             data={"event_id": "a" * 32, "timestamp": self.two_min_ago, "fingerprint": ["group_1"]},
 574             project_id=project.id,

 832         assert len(response.data["data"]) == 1
 833         data = response.data["data"]
 834         assert data[0]["failure_rate"] == 0.75

1375                 data={

1382                 project_id=project.id,
1383             )

1386             response = self.client.get(
1387                 self.url,

1389                 data={
1390                     "field": ["count(id)", "issue.id", "context.key"],
1391                     "sort": "-count_id",
1392                     "query": "language:C++",
1393                 },
1394             )
1395

1399             assert "field=issue.id" in link
1400             assert "field=count%28id%29" in link
1401             assert "field=context.key" in link
1402             assert "sort=-count_id" in link
1403             assert "query=language%3AC%2B%2B" in link
1404 
1405         assert len(response.data["data"]) == 2

1408         assert data[1]["count_id"] == 1

1599     def test_issue_in_search_and_columns(self):
1600         self.login_as(user=self.user)
1601 
1602         project1 = self.create_project()
1603         project2 = self.create_project()
1604         event1 = self.store_event(
1605             data={
1606                 "event_id": "a" * 32,
1607                 "transaction": "/example",
1608                 "message": "how to make fast",
1609                 "timestamp": self.two_min_ago,
1610                 "fingerprint": ["group_1"],
1611             },
1612             project_id=project1.id,
1613         )
1614         self.store_event(
1615             data={
1616                 "event_id": "b" * 32,
1617                 "transaction": "/example",
1618                 "message": "how to make fast",
1619                 "timestamp": self.two_min_ago,
1620                 "fingerprint": ["group_1"],
1621             },
1622             project_id=project2.id,
1623         )
1624 
1625         tests = [
1626             ("issue", "issue:%s" % event1.group.qualified_short_id),
1627             ("issue.id", "issue:%s" % event1.group.qualified_short_id),
1628             ("issue", "issue.id:%s" % event1.group_id),
1629             ("issue.id", "issue.id:%s" % event1.group_id),
1630         ]
1631 
1632         with self.feature(
1633             {"organizations:discover-basic": True, "organizations:global-views": True}
1634         ):
1635             for testdata in tests:
1636                 response = self.client.get(
1637                     self.url, format="json", data={"field": [testdata[0]], "query": testdata[1]}
1638                 )
1639 
1640                 assert response.status_code == 200, response.content
1641                 data = response.data["data"]
1642                 assert len(data) == 1
1643                 assert data[0]["id"] == event1.event_id
1644                 assert data[0]["issue.id"] == event1.group_id
1645                 if testdata[0] == "issue":
1646                     assert data[0]["issue"] == event1.group.qualified_short_id
1647                 else:
1648                     assert data[0].get("issue", None) is None

2419     def test_context_fields(self):
2420         self.login_as(user=self.user)
2421         project = self.create_project()
2422         data = load_data("android")
2423         transaction_data = load_data("transaction")
2424         data["spans"] = transaction_data["spans"]
2425         data["contexts"]["trace"] = transaction_data["contexts"]["trace"]
2426         data["type"] = "transaction"
2427         data["transaction"] = "/failure_rate/1"
2428         data["timestamp"] = iso_format(before_now(minutes=1))
2429         data["start_timestamp"] = iso_format(before_now(minutes=1, seconds=5))
2430         data["user"]["geo"] = {"country_code": "US", "region": "CA", "city": "San Francisco"}
2431         data["contexts"]["http"] = {
2432             "method": "GET",
2433             "referer": "something.something",
2434             "url": "https://areyouasimulation.com",
2435         }
2436         self.store_event(data, project_id=project.id)
2437 
2438         fields = [
2439             "http.method",
2440             "http.referer",
2441             "http.url",
2442             "os.build",
2443             "os.kernel_version",
2444             "device.arch",
2445             "device.battery_level",
2446             "device.brand",
2447             "device.charging",
2448             "device.locale",
2449             "device.model_id",
2450             "device.name",
2451             "device.online",
2452             "device.orientation",
2453             "device.simulator",
2454             "device.uuid",
2455         ]
2456 
2457         with self.feature("organizations:discover-basic"):
2458             response = self.client.get(
2459                 self.url,
2460                 format="json",
2461                 data={"field": fields + ["count()"], "query": "event.type:transaction"},
2462             )
2463 
2464         assert response.status_code == 200, response.content
2465         assert len(response.data["data"]) == 1
2466         results = response.data["data"]
2467 
2468         for field in fields:
2469             key, value = field.split(".", 1)
2470             expected = data["contexts"][key][value]
2471 
2472             # TODO (evanh) There is a bug in snuba right now where if a promoted column is used for a boolean
2473             # value, it returns "1" or "0" instead of "True" and "False" (not that those make more sense)
2474             if expected in (True, False):
2475                 expected = six.text_type(expected)
2476             # All context columns are treated as strings, regardless of the type of data they stored.
2477             elif isinstance(expected, six.integer_types):
2478                 expected = "{:.1f}".format(expected)
2479 
2480             assert results[0][field] == expected
2481         assert results[0]["count"] == 1

2483     @pytest.mark.xfail(reason="these fields behave differently between the types of events")
2484     def test_context_fields_in_errors(self):
2485         self.login_as(user=self.user)
2486         project = self.create_project()
2487         data = load_data("android")
2488         transaction_data = load_data(
2489             "transaction",
2490             timestamp=before_now(minutes=1),
2491             start_timestamp=before_now(minutes=1, seconds=5),
2492         )
2493         data["spans"] = transaction_data["spans"]
2494         data["contexts"]["trace"] = transaction_data["contexts"]["trace"]
2495         data["type"] = "error"
2496         data["transaction"] = "/failure_rate/1"
2497         data["user"]["geo"] = {"country_code": "US", "region": "CA", "city": "San Francisco"}
2498         data["contexts"]["http"] = {
2499             "method": "GET",
2500             "referer": "something.something",
2501             "url": "https://areyouasimulation.com",
2502         }
2503         self.store_event(data, project_id=project.id)
2504 
2505         fields = [
2506             "http.method",
2507             "http.referer",
2508             "http.url",
2509             "os.build",
2510             "os.kernel_version",
2511             "device.arch",
2512             "device.battery_level",
2513             "device.brand",
2514             "device.charging",
2515             "device.locale",
2516             "device.model_id",
2517             "device.name",
2518             "device.online",
2519             "device.orientation",
2520             "device.simulator",
2521             "device.uuid",
2522         ]
2523 
2524         with self.feature("organizations:discover-basic"):
2525             response = self.client.get(
2526                 self.url,
2527                 format="json",
2528                 data={"field": fields + ["count()"], "query": "event.type:error"},
2529             )
2530 
2531         assert response.status_code == 200, response.content
2532         assert len(response.data["data"]) == 1
2533         results = response.data["data"]
2534 
2535         for field in fields:
2536             key, value = field.split(".", 1)
2537             expected = data["contexts"][key][value]
2538 
2539             # TODO (evanh) There is a bug in snuba right now where if a promoted column is used for a boolean
2540             # value, it returns "1" or "0" instead of "True" and "False" (not that those make more sense)
2541             if expected in (True, False):
2542                 expected = six.text_type(expected)
2543             # All context columns are treated as strings, regardless of the type of data they stored.
2544             elif isinstance(expected, six.integer_types):
2545                 expected = "{:.1f}".format(expected)
2546 
2547             assert results[0][field] == expected
2548 
2549         assert results[0]["count"] == 1

2551     def test_histogram_function(self):
2552         self.login_as(user=self.user)
2553         project = self.create_project()
2554         start = before_now(minutes=2).replace(microsecond=0)
2555         latencies = [
2556             (1, 500, 5),
2557             (1000, 1500, 4),
2558             (3000, 3500, 3),
2559             (6000, 6500, 2),
2560             (10000, 10000, 1),  # just to make the math easy
2561         ]
2562         values = []
2563         for bucket in latencies:
2564             for i in range(bucket[2]):
2565                 # Don't generate a wide range of variance as the buckets can mis-align.
2566                 milliseconds = random.randint(bucket[0], bucket[1])
2567                 values.append(milliseconds)
2568                 data = load_data("transaction")
2569                 data["transaction"] = "/failure_rate/{}".format(milliseconds)
2570                 data["timestamp"] = iso_format(start)
2571                 data["start_timestamp"] = (start - timedelta(milliseconds=milliseconds)).isoformat()
2572                 self.store_event(data, project_id=project.id)
2573 
2574         with self.feature(
2575             {"organizations:discover-basic": True, "organizations:global-views": True}
2576         ):
2577             response = self.client.get(
2578                 self.url,
2579                 format="json",
2580                 data={
2581                     "field": ["histogram(transaction.duration, 10)", "count()"],
2582                     "query": "event.type:transaction",
2583                     "sort": "histogram_transaction_duration_10",
2584                 },
2585             )
2586         assert response.status_code == 200, response.content
2587         data = response.data["data"]
2588         assert len(data) == 11
2589         bucket_size = ceil((max(values) - min(values)) / 10.0)
2590         expected = [
2591             (0, 5),
2592             (bucket_size, 4),
2593             (bucket_size * 2, 0),
2594             (bucket_size * 3, 3),
2595             (bucket_size * 4, 0),
2596             (bucket_size * 5, 0),
2597             (bucket_size * 6, 2),
2598             (bucket_size * 7, 0),
2599             (bucket_size * 8, 0),
2600             (bucket_size * 9, 0),
2601             (bucket_size * 10, 1),
2602         ]
2603         for idx, datum in enumerate(data):
2604             assert datum["histogram_transaction_duration_10"] == expected[idx][0]
2605             assert datum["count"] == expected[idx][1]
2606 
2607     def test_histogram_function_with_filters(self):
2608         self.login_as(user=self.user)
2609         project = self.create_project()
2610         start = before_now(minutes=2).replace(microsecond=0)
2611         latencies = [
2612             (1, 500, 5),
2613             (1000, 1500, 4),
2614             (3000, 3500, 3),
2615             (6000, 6500, 2),
2616             (10000, 10000, 1),  # just to make the math easy
2617         ]
2618         values = []
2619         for bucket in latencies:
2620             for i in range(bucket[2]):
2621                 milliseconds = random.randint(bucket[0], bucket[1])
2622                 values.append(milliseconds)
2623                 data = load_data("transaction")
2624                 data["transaction"] = "/failure_rate/sleepy_gary/{}".format(milliseconds)
2625                 data["timestamp"] = iso_format(start)
2626                 data["start_timestamp"] = (start - timedelta(milliseconds=milliseconds)).isoformat()
2627                 self.store_event(data, project_id=project.id)
2628 
2629         # Add a transaction that totally throws off the buckets
2630         milliseconds = random.randint(bucket[0], bucket[1])
2631         data = load_data("transaction")
2632         data["transaction"] = "/failure_rate/hamurai"
2633         data["timestamp"] = iso_format(start)
2634         data["start_timestamp"] = iso_format(start - timedelta(milliseconds=1000000))
2635         self.store_event(data, project_id=project.id)
2636 
2637         with self.feature(
2638             {"organizations:discover-basic": True, "organizations:global-views": True}
2639         ):
2640             response = self.client.get(
2641                 self.url,
2642                 format="json",
2643                 data={
2644                     "field": ["histogram(transaction.duration, 10)", "count()"],
2645                     "query": "event.type:transaction transaction:/failure_rate/sleepy_gary*",
2646                     "sort": "histogram_transaction_duration_10",
2647                 },
2648             )
2649 
2650         assert response.status_code == 200, response.content
2651         data = response.data["data"]
2652         assert len(data) == 11
2653         bucket_size = ceil((max(values) - min(values)) / 10.0)
2654         expected = [
2655             (0, 5),
2656             (bucket_size, 4),
2657             (bucket_size * 2, 0),
2658             (bucket_size * 3, 3),
2659             (bucket_size * 4, 0),
2660             (bucket_size * 5, 0),
2661             (bucket_size * 6, 2),
2662             (bucket_size * 7, 0),
2663             (bucket_size * 8, 0),
2664             (bucket_size * 9, 0),
2665             (bucket_size * 10, 1),
2666         ]
2667         for idx, datum in enumerate(data):
2668             assert datum["histogram_transaction_duration_10"] == expected[idx][0]
2669             assert datum["count"] == expected[idx][1]

2671     @mock.patch("sentry.utils.snuba.quantize_time")
2672     def test_quantize_dates(self, mock_quantize):
2673         self.login_as(user=self.user)
2674         self.create_project()
2675         mock_quantize.return_value = before_now(days=1).replace(tzinfo=utc)
2676         with self.feature("organizations:discover-basic"):
2677             # Don't quantize short time periods
2678             self.client.get(
2679                 self.url,
2680                 format="json",
2681                 data={"statsPeriod": "1h", "query": "", "field": ["id", "timestamp"]},
2682             )
2683             # Don't quantize absolute date periods
2684             self.client.get(
2685                 self.url,
2686                 format="json",
2687                 data={
2688                     "start": iso_format(before_now(days=20)),
2689                     "end": iso_format(before_now(days=15)),
2690                     "query": "",
2691                     "field": ["id", "timestamp"],
2692                 },
2693             )
2694 
2695             assert len(mock_quantize.mock_calls) == 0
2696 
2697             # Quantize long date periods
2698             self.client.get(
2699                 self.url,
2700                 format="json",
2701                 data={"field": ["id", "timestamp"], "statsPeriod": "90d", "query": ""},
2702             )
2703 
2704             assert len(mock_quantize.mock_calls) == 2

2706     def test_limit_number_of_fields(self):
2707         self.login_as(user=self.user)
2708         self.create_project()
2709         with self.feature("organizations:discover-basic"):
2710             for i in range(1, 25):
2711                 response = self.client.get(self.url, {"field": ["id"] * i})
2712                 if i <= 20:
2713                     assert response.status_code == 200
2714                 else:
2715                     assert response.status_code == 400
2716                     assert (
2717                         response.data["detail"]
2718                         == "You can view up to 20 fields at a time. Please delete some and try again."
2719                     )
